{"sequence":19,"timestamp":"2026-04-15T13:33:50.503489459Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-dab9eb88","body":"finding_summary: `milestone show` / `milestone status` can report a bead count and `has_plan=true` from cached snapshot data after the live plan artifacts are gone. In `src/cli/milestone.rs:320-350`, `load_bead_count` falls back to `snapshot.progress.total_beads` when `plan.json` is missing, and `load_milestone_detail` then sets `has_plan` from that fallback count or `snapshot.plan_hash`. I verified this by creating a milestone with only `milestone.toml` + `status.json`: `milestone show --json` still reported `bead_count: 7` and `has_plan: true` with no `plan.json` present.\nseverity: medium\naffected_files: [\"src/cli/milestone.rs\"]\nremediation_hint: For `show`/`status`, derive plan presence and bead count from the live plan artifacts only, or surface a clear missing-plan error instead of falling back to `status.json` counters.","dedup_key":"f6559d30c2153cbc78c935a9a548db655e32998d7631aa8cd1b4e3c0dbefa5b5","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260415130611","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":20,"timestamp":"2026-04-15T13:33:50.512792058Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-422d6518","body":"finding_summary: `milestone plan` treats a successfully started milestone requirements run as a hard failure whenever the full-mode pipeline opens a question round. `src/cli/milestone.rs:146-166` immediately calls `extract_milestone_bundle_handoff` after `draft_milestone`, but `draft_milestone` only guarantees a run ID (`src/contexts/requirements_drafting/service.rs:188-220`) and the requirements pipeline can validly stop in `awaiting_answers` (`src/contexts/requirements_drafting/service.rs:1089-1248`). The extractor explicitly rejects any non-`completed` run (`src/contexts/requirements_drafting/service.rs:2319-2333`), so a milestone that needs clarification exits non-zero even though planning actually started.\nseverity: high\naffected_files: [\"src/cli/milestone.rs\", \"src/contexts/requirements_drafting/service.rs\"]\nremediation_hint: After `draft_milestone`, inspect the run status before extracting the handoff. Treat `awaiting_answers` as a successful intermediate result that prints the run ID and next-step instructions, and only extract/materialize when the run is actually completed.","dedup_key":"06d9a45185c4c1ede6d6d56b2b327ad7aa1753ac83304162fc4aa5f0aeec6ea6","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260415130611","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":21,"timestamp":"2026-04-15T13:33:50.521999668Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-95b67e72","body":"handle_show (line 200) and handle_status (line 222) in src/cli/milestone.rs skip workspace governance validation (load_workspace_config / ensure_supported_workspace_version). Every other CLI handler in the codebase—including read-only ones like project show (project.rs:631) and project list (project.rs:599)—validates the workspace version first. Without this check, milestone show/status on a workspace with an unsupported version will produce confusing filesystem errors instead of the clear 'unsupported workspace version' message. Fix: add the same two-line validation block at the top of handle_show and handle_status, matching the pattern in handle_create.","dedup_key":"996ac6cc3ba7a33596f55edfbb16ad53d13a8aa2ba5a0ae3d7a85102f0c2c718","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"claude","model_id":"claude-opus-4-6-max","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260415130611","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
