{"sequence":40,"timestamp":"2026-04-15T14:02:18.872832333Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-66b860a6","body":"finding_summary: \"`milestone plan` cannot complete the documented clarification workflow. In `src/cli/milestone.rs:141-170`, every invocation immediately starts a fresh `draft_milestone()` run and only then inspects that new run's status, yet the `awaiting_answers` branch tells the operator to run `requirements answer <run_id>` and rerun `milestone plan`. After answers are submitted, rerunning `milestone plan` ignores the answered run and launches a new requirements run instead of materializing the completed bundle.\"\nseverity: high\naffected_files:\n- src/cli/milestone.rs\nremediation_hint: \"Persist the milestone's in-flight requirements run ID, and on rerun inspect that existing run first: if it is now completed, materialize its bundle; if it is still awaiting answers, keep pointing the user at that same run instead of redrafting.\"","dedup_key":"e39f07de14cf15d80f129cd97ae2e9598572b0b5c271cd77c9183d54ef0a1a10","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260415130611","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":41,"timestamp":"2026-04-15T14:02:18.881352937Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-5a4a19dc","body":"finding_summary: \"`milestone show` and `milestone status` trust raw `plan.json` without validating that it matches the current snapshot. In `src/cli/milestone.rs:353-399`, the commands parse `plan.json` directly and derive `bead_count`/`has_plan` from it, but they do not perform the plan-hash check or bundle validation that `project create-from-bead` already uses in `src/cli/project.rs:721-819`. A stale or semantically corrupt plan can therefore be reported as live milestone state instead of surfacing corruption.\"\nseverity: medium\naffected_files:\n- src/cli/milestone.rs\nremediation_hint: \"Route show/status through the same validated milestone-plan loader used by project creation, so these commands either report a snapshot-consistent plan or fail with a milestone-specific corruption error.\"","dedup_key":"7ac931fda5f0e278671d16b306473f70d111b2ebc3f0a8d467c0e4eb03f0c598","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260415130611","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
