{"sequence":100,"timestamp":"2026-04-15T15:30:45.618471930Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-5-7597c84a","body":"finding_summary: If the CLI is interrupted after writing a __starting__ reservation, milestone planning becomes permanently wedged. reserve_pending_requirements_run rejects any prefixed pending_requirements_run_id at src/cli/milestone.rs:723-728, but that marker is only replaced after draft_milestone returns from the full requirements pipeline at src/cli/milestone.rs:667-688 and src/contexts/requirements_drafting/service.rs:188-217. A killed plan command therefore leaves no recovery path for later milestone plan invocations. severity: high affected_files: [\"src/cli/milestone.rs:667-688\", \"src/cli/milestone.rs:723-735\", \"src/contexts/requirements_drafting/service.rs:188-217\"] remediation_hint: Persist the real run_id before the long-running pipeline starts, or add stale-reservation timeout/ownership recovery instead of treating every __starting__ marker as live forever.","dedup_key":"bf4235f6ce3e5b15e182e2a8fe1541fa73a92386b95f00a7f69103c91b0acd89","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260415130611","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":101,"timestamp":"2026-04-15T15:30:45.627111696Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-5-9618b042","body":"finding_summary: Replanning an already ready/completed/failed milestone never updates the exposed status to show that planning is underway or awaiting answers. The reservation path only sets pending_requirements_run_id at src/cli/milestone.rs:714-735, handle_plan returns early on awaiting_answers at src/cli/milestone.rs:154-161, and both summary/detail views serialize snapshot.status directly while omitting the pending run at src/cli/milestone.rs:61-89 and src/cli/milestone.rs:355-395. As a result, milestone show/status can continue reporting 'ready' or 'completed' even while a replan is blocked on clarification. severity: medium affected_files: [\"src/cli/milestone.rs:61-89\", \"src/cli/milestone.rs:154-161\", \"src/cli/milestone.rs:355-395\", \"src/cli/milestone.rs:714-735\"] remediation_hint: Either derive an effective display status from pending_requirements_run_id and the referenced requirements run, or transition the milestone snapshot back to planning while a replan is outstanding and expose the pending run in the JSON/detail output.","dedup_key":"f4256aedd3adf7fdef1ace116c8591f762a74d2d97449e4106ac9e3e1eb47ef2","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260415130611","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":102,"timestamp":"2026-04-15T15:30:45.640102898Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-5-b5b04d7d","body":"finding_summary: load_pending_requirements_run silently clears the pending pointer for every read_run failure at src/cli/milestone.rs:615-620, even though the filesystem adapter distinguishes missing runs from corrupt or otherwise unreadable run.json files at src/adapters/fs.rs:5427-5440. A malformed or transiently unreadable requirements/<run>/run.json will therefore be treated as stale state and replaced by a brand-new planning run, orphaning the original clarification/bundle data instead of surfacing the underlying corruption. severity: medium affected_files: [\"src/cli/milestone.rs:615-620\", \"src/adapters/fs.rs:5427-5440\"] remediation_hint: Only clear pending_requirements_run_id for a definite not-found/stale case; propagate CorruptRecord and other I/O failures so operators can repair the existing requirements run rather than forking a new one.","dedup_key":"8a3d9f27793b66d70040577628b52bfd53f49ea6c55173a6a72b388847b73365","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260415130611","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
